Client identifier - 64 byte string set to identify the client.
- oci_set_client_identifier
- appears in the database as:
    - v$SESSION.CLIENT_IDENTIFIER
    - v$ACTIVE_SESSION_HISTORY.CLIENT_ID
    - DBA_HIST_ACTIVE_SESS_HISTORY.CLIENT_ID

Client information - 64 byte string set to describe the client.
- oci_set_client_info
- appears in the database as:
    - v$SESSION.CLIENT_INFO

Module Name - 48 byte string that describes the module currently using the session.
- oci_set_module_name
- appears in the database as:
    - v$SESSION.MODULE
    - v$SQL.MODULE
    - v$SQLAREA.MODULE
    - v$ACTIVE_SESSION_HISTORY.MODULE
    - DBA_HIST_ACTIVE_SESS_HISTORY.MODULE
    - DBA_HIST_SQLSTAT.MODULE

Action Name - 32 byte string describing the action being processed.
- oci_set_action
- appears in the database as:
    - v$SESSION.ACTION
    - v$SQL.ACTION
    - v$SQLAREA.ACTION
    - v$ACTIVE_SESSION_HISTORY.ACTION
    - v$SQLAREA_PLAN_HASH.ACTION
    - DBA_HIST_ACTIVE_SESS_HISTORY.ACTION
    - DBA_HIST_SQLSTAT.ACTION
    - ALL_SQLSET_STATEMENTS.ACTION
